{"TopicId":132253,"ForumId":29,"TopicTitle":"Is there a better way to tell when flight scene is stabilized?","CreatedByName":"linuxgurugamer","CreatedById":129964,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-02-16T13:39:51Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"linuxgurugamer","CreatedById":129964,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-02-16T13:39:51Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI need to know when the flight scene is stabilized, and so far the only way I have figured out is the following:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cpre class=\u0022ipsCode\u0022\u003E\nif (FlightGlobals.fetch.activeVessel.ctrlState.mainThrottle \u0026gt; 0) {\u003C/pre\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nKSP doesn\u0027t set the throttle to 50% until everything is go for launch. \u00A0Is there a better way? \u00A0I\u0027m concerned that if there is another mod which sets the throttle to 0 for launch, it might happen before mine and I would never know everything is stable.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis is for a simulation mod, which is always launched from inside the editor.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"sarbian","CreatedById":57146,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-02-16T13:45:07Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHave you tried\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cpre class=\u0022ipsCode prettyprint prettyprinted\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003Eif\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E \u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E(\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan\u003EFlightGlobals\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E.\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan\u003Eready\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E)\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E \u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E{...}\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/pre\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Crzyrndm","CreatedById":92871,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-02-16T19:42:32Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI prefer\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cpre class=\u0022ipsCode prettyprint prettyprinted\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003Eif\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E \u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E(\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan\u003EActiveVessel\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E.\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan\u003EholdPhysics\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E)\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E\n  \u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan\u003Ereturn\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E;\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E...\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/pre\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI find FlightGlobals.ready sets true just a little too early in some cases (just have to be aware holdphysics goes true when using time warp)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"linuxgurugamer","CreatedById":129964,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-02-17T17:11:58Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222412700\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022132253\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221455630307\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002257146\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022sarbian\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 2/16/2016 at 8:45 AM, sarbian said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHave you tried\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cpre class=\u0022ipsCode prettyprint prettyprinted\u0022\u003E\n\n\u003Cspan\u003Eif\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E \u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E(\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan\u003EFlightGlobals\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E.\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan\u003Eready\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E)\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E \u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E{...}\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/pre\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes, and it wasn\u0027t really ready. \u00A0Planet exploded :-)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m going to try what @crzyrndm suggested.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nRight now, I have a workaround by watching the throttle, but this would be better\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks to both you and Crzyrndm for the suggestions\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"linuxgurugamer","CreatedById":129964,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-02-17T18:52:50Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nUsing the FlightGlobals.ready will be a big plus for when I start doing sims from an already-launched ship\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}